				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h3>&#8220;Get Current Address&#8221;</h3>
<h4>A Pythonista Script running on iPhone:</h4><p>&#8220;Get Current Address&#8221; is a <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/pythonista/id528579881?mt=8 target=">pythonista</a> script I created based on some google research. I wanted to take advantage of the iphone&#8217;s geolocation and geocoding abilities.</p><p>I was also attempting to fill a very small niche. Although google maps and apple maps are good at showing where you are and where a certain address is, there is no built in functionality to quickly show you the address at which you and your phone are currently positioned within.</p><p>It can also output course direction and speed when the phone is moving.</p>
